Shares of Nio Inc. NIO, -3.65% slid 5% in very active trading Thursday, to start the new year with a pullback after ending 2019 with a two-day surge of 66%. Trading volume topped 20 million shares, enough to make the stock the most actively traded by far on the NYSE. The China-based electric vehicle maker's stock soared the past two sessions after the company reported better-than-expected quarterly results and provided an upbeat outlook for the latest quarter. The stock has now run up 142% over the past three months, while shares of rival Tesla Inc. TSLA, +4.75% have climbed 74% and the S&P 500 SPX, +0.22% has gained 12%.